This file provides an example of the environment variables needed for LexiSense.

Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values.

DO NOT commit the .env file to version control.

--- Security ---

A long, random string used to sign the session ID cookie.

You can generate one here: https://www.google.com/search?q=https://generate-secret.now.sh/32

SESSION_SECRET=your_super_secret_session_key

--- Database ---

The connection string for your Neon serverless PostgreSQL database.

Find this in your Neon project dashboard.

DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@host/dbname?sslmode=require

--- AI Service ---

Your API key for the OpenAI service.

Find this in your OpenAI account dashboard.

OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-your_openai_api_key_here

--- File Storage (Optional for local dev) ---

In a real production environment, you would configure these for your S3 bucket.

The mock service will use defaults if these are not set.

S3_BUCKET_NAME=your-production-bucket-name

AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-aws-access-key

AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-aws-secret-key

AWS_REGION=your-aws-region
